<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1106,496,558]" box="[189,1106,531,558]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">MEASUREMENTS. DSL 3.77, DSW 3.19, femur I 2.38, II 4.80, III 3.25, IV 4.49.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1399,598,802]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
DORSUM (
<figureCitation box="[305,434,598,624]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,431,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-47@12.[189,1398,425,1848]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 7. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628985/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 7A, C</figureCitation>
). Blunt PAM; acuminate median paracheliceral projection similar in size to PAM. High ocularium with median spine (about twice times ocularium height). Carapace with scattered granules. Scutal areas I–IV with scattered granules with some tubercles among them. Posterior margin of dorsal scutum with scattered granules. Lateral margins with blunt tubercles about the same size as those on the scUtUm. Free tergites I–III with a defined row of granUles. Anal opercUlUm with scattered granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[188,1399,842,904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
VENTER (
<figureCitation box="[299,390,842,869]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,431,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-47@12.[189,1398,425,1848]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 7. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628985/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Coxa I with irregular row of setiferous tubercles, coxae II–IV densely and irregularly granulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1179,944,970]" box="[189,1179,944,970]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">CHELICERAE. Segment I with two ectal-basal tubercles and one mesal-basal tubercle.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1399,1010,1072]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">PEDIPALPS. Trochanter with sparse tubercles dorsally. Femur with one mesal apical setiferous tubercle. Tibia setation: ectal IiIi, mesal IiIi; tarsus setation: ectal IIIi, mesal IIi.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1400,1111,1245]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
LEGS (
<figureCitation box="[267,338,1111,1138]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[254,1324,265,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[254,1334,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386). A–B. Femur IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. C–D. Femur III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. E–F. Patella and tibia IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. G–H. Patella and tibia III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. I– J. Detail of trochanter IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. Scale bars: A–H = 0.5 mm; I–J = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628987" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628987/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Coxae I–III with scattered granules; coxa IV with one transversal, prolateral and apical apophysis, which is conical and short. Trochanters I–IV with scattered tubercles; trochanter IV with one probasal apophysis, which is conical, short and dorsally oriented. Femur III with proventral and retroventral rows of acute tubercles increasing in size apically; tibia III with proventral and retroventral
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628989" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4628989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628989/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50" startId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" targetBox="[189,1398,1293,1925]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1399,1963,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
