</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="15.[188,1400,265,362]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">rows of acuminate tubercles. Femur IV slightly sinuous, with small PDS and RDS, proventral row of acuminate tubercles increasing in size apically and retroventral row with reduced tubercles; tibia IV with proventral and retroventral rows of acuminate tubercles increasing in size subapically.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,401,533]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">
PENIS (
<figureCitation box="[274,349,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1293,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-252@14.[189,1398,1293,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), distal part of penis. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Right lateral view. Scale bars = 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628989/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Ventral plate with substraight lateral margins; distal margin slightly concave; ventral surface entirely covered with 
<typeStatus box="[549,600,437,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
T1 microsetae; with three pairs of lateral-distal MS C1–C3, three pairs of A1, one pair of B1, one pair of minute D1 and E1 absent. Stylus with ventrally-tilted medianventral trichomes. Ventral process tUbUlar, cUrved, with apex with flabelliform projection.
</paragraph>
